Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.22,0:01:45.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dracula Manor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.75,0:01:52.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Most of Mr. Torakura's novels are centered around vampires,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.22,0:01:55.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he's earned the nickname "Mr. Dracula."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.53,0:01:57.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why it's called Dracula Manor?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.63,0:02:00.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Daisuke Torakura a famous writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.70,0:02:04.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the most popular writer in the Japan Horror Novel Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.67,0:02:09.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's even started to branch out into heroic fantasy novels,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.41,0:02:12.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and is gaining female fans, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.01,0:02:13.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure know a lot about him, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.91,0:02:18.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do! I {\i1}am{\i0} a brilliant detective, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.62,0:02:22.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.52,0:02:26.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Horror Times Monthly{\i0}â€”\NSpecial Daisuke Torakura Issue!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.86,0:02:29.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, a cheat sheet, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.76,0:02:31.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.70,0:02:36.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.77,0:02:42.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's{\i0} Dracula Manor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.00,0:03:13.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.45,0:03:13.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.97,0:03:15.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming all this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.91,0:03:17.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.90,0:03:20.99,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshiya Tadokoro (26)\NStudent of Daisuke Torakura
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.44,0:03:21.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tadokoro, I'm studying under Torakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.78,0:03:25.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been waiting for you. Come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.66,0:03:32.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.21,0:03:36.04,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Etsuko Torakura (30)\NDaisuke Torakura's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.69,0:03:36.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.04,0:03:39.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a beautiful woman! I'm jealous!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:41.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.33,0:03:43.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.57,0:03:51.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Old mansions certainly have a unique feel to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.71,0:03:54.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get a chill down my spine for some reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.51,0:03:58.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.82,0:04:04.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.32,0:04:07.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Might you be Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.79,0:04:10.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.06,0:04:13.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it! It's an honor to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.00,0:04:20.13,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Fumio Doi (48)\NChief Editor, Horror Times Monthly
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.27,0:04:20.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Doi, editor in chief for Daigakukan's {\i1}Horror Times Monthly{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.13,0:04:23.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know that magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.04,0:04:26.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, so {\i1}you're{\i0} the famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.39,0:04:32.77,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Shuichi Hamura (33)\NNorth Kanto University Folklore Researcher
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.85,0:04:28.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Shuichi Hamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.98,0:04:33.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a folklore researcher at North Kanto University.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.09,0:04:36.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What sort of research do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.79,0:04:41.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mainly... vampire legends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.53,0:04:44.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh. That's {\i1}interesting{\i0} research...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.96,0:04:47.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, where's Mr. Torakura?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.23,0:04:49.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in the study, writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.24,0:04:55.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's... a study room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.45,0:05:03.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.02,0:05:09.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A black-out curtain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.90,0:05:28.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a movie...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.41,0:05:31.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.88,0:05:34.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to Dracula Manor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.91,0:05:38.54,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Daisuke Torakura (50)\NHorror Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.68,0:05:38.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Daisuke Torakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.23,0:05:51.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Octagonal rooms certainly are rare...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.80,0:05:57.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... do you always dress up like Dracula like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.10,0:06:03.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By writing while cloaked in Dracula attire as I play Dracula films,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.44,0:06:07.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought many a masterpiece into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.95,0:06:11.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.38,0:06:17.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to hire you to investigate the behavior of my wife, Etsuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.46,0:06:20.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Behavior? An affair, in other words?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.63,0:06:21.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.86,0:06:28.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to find definitive proof of the affair, and the man it's with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.17,0:06:32.64,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Bastard called me all the way out here just for some stupid affair...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.64,0:06:37.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am willing to pay one million yen, and related expenses, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.08,0:06:39.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly! I gladly accept the job!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.68,0:06:46.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn. I didn't bring any chains for the car...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.62,0:06:51.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No worries. You may spend the night here, in Dracula Manor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.16,0:06:56.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll do that, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.94,0:07:12.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a lovely smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.61,0:07:15.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's homemade rosemary tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.05,0:07:20.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And dinner was delicious, too! You're a good cook, Tadokoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:24.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to him, the lady of the house\Ncan live an easy, carefree life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.99,0:07:26.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.59,0:07:33.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm studying novel-writing here,\Nso it's only natural that I help out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:38.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Great. I look forward to your new series starting next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.70,0:07:42.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, I must finish this month's manuscript first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.71,0:07:46.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro, bring wine and a movie to the study.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.88,0:07:51.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. What movie would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.42,0:07:53.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.52,0:08:03.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say! Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Want to come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.09,0:08:05.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's lots of rare stuff to see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.13,0:08:06.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Rare stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.97,0:08:10.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He means Torakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s prized "Dracula Collection,"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.30,0:08:13.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,full of props and costumes from vampire films.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.87,0:08:15.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go see, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.87,0:08:17.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.78,0:08:19.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.72,0:08:33.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His vast collection of props and films are kept in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.86,0:08:38.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where do these stairs go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.73,0:08:41.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's a library in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.27,0:08:46.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's filled with vampire books and old texts from around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.17,0:08:49.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A Dracula Library, you could call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.35,0:08:55.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, a Dracula mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.71,0:08:57.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A Dracula hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.02,0:09:01.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A cross sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.45,0:09:04.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this one'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:06.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you decided on a movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:10.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. An old British movie called {\i1}Banquet of Fresh Blood{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.53,0:09:12.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He just loves this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.93,0:09:15.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See that wooden stake there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.67,0:09:21.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was driven through the vampire's heart in the last scene of this film.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.37,0:09:26.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In his study, he also has the cross the vampire was strung up on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.78,0:09:30.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Huh? I smell oil paint...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.32,0:09:33.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's odd. There aren't any oil paintings...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.65,0:09:35.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.22,0:09:36.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.42,0:09:38.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.52,0:09:42.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to ask, but could you make sure all the windows are locked?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.29,0:09:45.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, no problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.44,0:09:56.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.27,0:09:57.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.38,0:10:08.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you think of the Dracula Collection?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:10.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was kind of gross!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.60,0:10:21.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Dracula is just fiction, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.63,0:10:24.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that the Count Dracula we know
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.54,0:10:33.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was a monster created by Bram Stoker\Nin his 1897 novel, {\i1}Dracula{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.38,0:10:37.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, there {\i1}were{\i0} several noblemen in medieval Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.82,0:10:43.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who were feared as vampires because of the atrocities they committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.22,0:10:49.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Torakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} has collected many old documents concerning that,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.03,0:10:53.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which is why I visit here personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.31,0:11:10.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Want to play cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.58,0:11:11.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.82,0:11:16.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! Hold on while I make sure everything's locked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.79,0:11:27.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} seems really nice, does he like horror novels, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.70,0:11:32.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, I'd say he's probably more into fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.07,0:11:35.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who introduced him to Torakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.61,0:11:38.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed to have real talent, you see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.75,0:11:44.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it still snowing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.92,0:11:46.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's stopped now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.26,0:11:54.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you two play cards with us, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.26,0:11:59.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I have a headache, so I'm going to bed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.86,0:12:05.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'd like to browse the library a bit more. If you'll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.91,0:12:16.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Use your 6 of Hearts already!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.68,0:12:19.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.05,0:12:22.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And my theory was right on the mark!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.49,0:12:23.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.56,0:12:27.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you join us, Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.39,0:12:32.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is retelling his many exploits!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.30,0:12:35.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:39.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to use the restroom. I've been feeling ill since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.64,0:12:41.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.41,0:12:45.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.39,0:12:57.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad. We're going to bed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.89,0:13:01.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You do that. It's grownup time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.89,0:13:04.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.56,0:13:06.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.23,0:13:08.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't answer the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.57,0:13:10.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You think maybe he dozed off?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.94,0:13:16.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd never do that! Late nights and alcohol never affect him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.91,0:13:19.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.91,0:13:22.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.61,0:13:24.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}! Say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.68,0:13:25.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Torakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.77,0:13:27.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.95,0:13:31.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.12,0:13:33.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.26,0:13:36.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am! Your husband isn't responding to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.69,0:13:39.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.60,0:13:42.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear the projector!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.53,0:13:46.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be! Shouldn't the movie be long over by now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.64,0:13:49.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go outside and call for him from the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.44,0:13:50.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.41,0:13:54.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.88,0:14:00.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The window's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.32,0:14:04.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the snow by the window's been trampled on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.29,0:14:05.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.19,0:14:10.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Torakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Are you in here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.50,0:14:13.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.97,0:14:17.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.28,0:14:19.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.66,0:14:50.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All the windows, but the one we entered from, are fixed in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.30,0:14:52.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.78,0:15:02.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the only door is locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.49,0:15:11.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Rubber sealing...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.56,0:15:15.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It'd be impossible to use string to lock it from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:20.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would appear the killer entered and exited through that window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.97,0:15:25.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, how did the killer get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.60,0:15:28.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the snow in front of the window was trampled...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.64,0:15:31.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there were no other footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.48,0:15:34.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Climbing up the cliff would be impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.41,0:15:39.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the rough waves in the lake would quickly capsize any boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:42.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, even with the window open,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.25,0:15:46.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this study room was still as good as locked...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.36,0:15:47.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did the police say?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.37,0:15:49.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.03,0:15:53.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The snowstorm caused an avalanche that blocked the only road here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.53,0:15:57.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They say they can't clear the road until at least morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.04,0:16:01.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn... Looks like {\i1}I'll{\i0} have to examine the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.77,0:16:04.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a vulgar murderer,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.38,0:16:09.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,killing him with a wooden stake,\Nas if he were Dracula...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.58,0:16:13.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and sticking his body on a cross, on top of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.82,0:16:15.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hold on, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:20.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why did the killer move the projector and light up the body?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.09,0:16:23.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Is there some reason behind it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:25.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost like the last scene of {\i1}Banquet of Fresh Blood{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.90,0:16:28.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Banquet of Fresh Blood{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.07,0:16:30.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the movie Tadokoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} brought him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.90,0:16:32.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.27,0:16:36.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Torakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s most beloved vampire film.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.91,0:16:42.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the killer set it up to look like the movie's last scene?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.28,0:16:46.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Rigor mortis has set in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.59,0:16:51.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning he's probably been dead for at least an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.16,0:16:59.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, the time of the murder was between 9:00 and 11:00 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.67,0:17:03.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a wound on the back of his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.04,0:17:06.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been hit with this. There's some blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.84,0:17:08.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.11,0:17:12.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was strung up and impaled with the stake after being knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.91,0:17:16.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, that stake came from the collection room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.58,0:17:18.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.32,0:17:25.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, the killer snuck in and stole the stake
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.56,0:17:28.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after Tadokoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came to get the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.16,0:17:31.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, after Tadokoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} delivered the movie to the study room,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.33,0:17:33.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the person murdered Mr. Torakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.57,0:17:35.83,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.83,0:17:38.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It doesn't smell like oil paint...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.54,0:17:43.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But all the windows were locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:50.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's not a single footprint outside the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.35,0:17:54.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the killer is an insider!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.03,0:18:04.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mister! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.36,0:18:07.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The end of a twig...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:09.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's got nothin' to do with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.84,0:18:11.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.57,0:18:14.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who could've stolen the stake
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.54,0:18:18.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is you, who went to browse the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:21.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.91,0:18:27.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, how exactly did I take the stake to the study?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.82,0:18:32.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I would've had to pass through the living room, where you all were.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.96,0:18:34.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.86,0:18:36.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There {\i1}is{\i0} one way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.63,0:18:37.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.46,0:18:40.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By going upstairs and walking across the corridor's roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.63,0:18:43.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You could get to the study that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.27,0:18:46.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.27,0:18:50.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your help! I already knew that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.24,0:18:55.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If I wanted to leave, I would still have to go through the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.41,0:18:57.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, I couldn't have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:18:59.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.22,0:19:00.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.35,0:19:04.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your room is above the collection room, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.53,0:19:10.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, you conspired with Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.10,0:19:12.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you saying, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.90,0:19:17.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}could{\i0} dangle a rope to the collection room window from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.87,0:19:21.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} used it to climb up to your room,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.37,0:19:24.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then traversed the corridor roof to reach the study.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.64,0:19:29.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He then scaled the roof there and set down in front of that window.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.15,0:19:32.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, he called out to Mr. Torakura to let him inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.92,0:19:35.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then murdered him when he got the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.19,0:19:39.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He used the same course in reverse to get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.26,0:19:41.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.23,0:19:43.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.00,0:19:47.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and I need to conspire to kill my husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:51.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Torakura suspected you of having an affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.67,0:19:56.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, were you having an affair with Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.11,0:19:58.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What makes you think we're...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.41,0:20:01.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Etsuko, let's not hide the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.01,0:20:02.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.48,0:20:05.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The police would find out right away, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.92,0:20:08.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you admit it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.75,0:20:13.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I do. But, we truly love each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.63,0:20:16.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the only one I love!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.96,0:20:19.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I never once loved Torakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.87,0:20:22.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you get married?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.77,0:20:31.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eight years ago, my father's business took a nosedive
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.08,0:20:34.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and was on the verge of bankruptcy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.48,0:20:37.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Torakura was an old acquaintance of my father's,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.15,0:20:39.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and in exchange for financing the business,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.99,0:20:44.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he demanded my hand in marriage after I had just graduated college!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.99,0:20:46.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the company went bankrupt,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.63,0:20:49.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so many people, and families, would be affected!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.56,0:20:53.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I had no choice but to...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.13,0:20:57.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We later learned that the business' downfall
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.14,0:21:00.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was actually because of Torakura's behind-the-scenes dirty work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.91,0:21:06.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, by the time we found out,\Nthe company was already in his name,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.14,0:21:09.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he threatened to destroy the company if we divorced...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.25,0:21:11.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's horrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.58,0:21:13.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.09,0:21:18.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Mr. Torakura died, his wife would inherit his company...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.76,0:21:19.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.99,0:21:23.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It wasn't us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.63,0:21:28.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have proof that we killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.57,0:21:32.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. If that's how you want it, then I'll show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.21,0:21:39.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You left her room, climbed onto the corridor roof from this window,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.81,0:21:41.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and went to the study.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.55,0:21:44.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The old guy's on the ball today!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.32,0:21:49.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s footprints are still on the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.39,0:21:54.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-There aren't any footprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.06,0:21:55.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.83,0:22:00.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.40,0:22:02.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's not a single footprint!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.33,0:22:08.91,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}With the corridor unusable,\Nthis roof was the only way to the study!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.91,0:22:17.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don't tell me the killer actually flew through the air, like a vampire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.04,0:23:47.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Leave the rest to me, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.91,0:23:56.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I thought only Hamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could have taken the stake,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.35,0:24:00.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but actually, anyone could have stolen it from outside!
